1. Sheet structure (one tab)
Create one Google Sheet tab named: Asset Inventory – Kahana Oasis.
​

Use one row per asset (hardware, software, cloud, data store, vendor, etc.).

2. Recommended columns
Copy‑paste these as your header row:

Asset ID

Category (Hardware / Software / Cloud / Data Store / Network / Vendor / Credential)

Asset Name

Description

Owner (Role or Person)

Business Function (Product, Engineering, Finance, HR, Support, etc.)

Environment (Prod / Staging / Dev / Corp / Other)

Location (Office / Remote / Cloud region)

Data Processed (None / Internal / Customer / Personal / Sensitive)

Data Classification (Public / Internal / Confidential / Regulated)

Criticality (Critical / High / Medium / Low)

Internet‑Exposed? (Yes/No)

Vendor / Provider (if applicable)

Licence / Contract Type (Per‑user, Subscription, Open source, etc.)

Licence / Contract Expiry Date

Configuration / Key Details (OS / Version / SKU / instance type, etc.)

Encryption at Rest? (Yes/No/Not applicable)

Encryption in Transit? (Yes/No/Not applicable)

Authentication Method (SSO, Local, API key, Service account)

Date Added

Lifecycle Status (In use / In build / Retired)

These fields align with SOC 2 guidance that inventories must cover hardware, software, cloud resources, data stores, and vendors with owners, classification, lifecycle and configuration details.

